Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper discusses the use of deep Q-learning strategies for learning to play families of text-based computer adventure games, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
2. cs.CL - The paper deals with text-based environments and natural language processing techniques are used to understand and interact with the game environment.
3. cs.LG - The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques for learning to play text-based adventure games, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
4. cs.HC - The paper discusses the use of curriculum learning and common sense reasoning to improve the learning performance of the agent, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction.
5. cs.SD - The paper deals with the task of learning to play families of text-based adventure games, which falls under the domain of game development and simulation.
